item.title: ATTACK THE BLOCK - Official Green Band Trailer - In Select Cities 7/29
item.description:
ATTACK THE BLOCK - Official Green Band Trailer - In Select Cities 7/29
For RESTRICTED content go to http://www.facebook.com/AttackTheBlockMovie Attack the Block Starring John Boyega and Jodie Whittaker. Directed by Joe Cornish From the producers of Shaun of the Dead and Hot Fuzz, ATTACK THE BLOCK follows a gang of tough inner-city kids who try to defend their turf against an invasion of savage alien creatures, turning a South London apartment complex into an extraterrestrial warzone. "a dazzling action-adventure comedy" "This year's District 9" - Jordan Hoffman, UGO   "An awesome film!" "One of the best of the year" -Alan Cerny, Ain't It Cool News   "Attack The Block is an unquestionable homerun and the kind of film that doesn't come around often enough." -David Harley, Bloody-Disgusting.com "Aliens rip the bloody hell out of gangbangers in the London projects. Done on the indie cheap with untold riches in ballsy imagination, this knockout creature feature busts the Hollywood chops of Cowboys and Aliens. It's hot, fierce, funny, vicious and ready to bite, baby. Attack gets its teeth from writer-director Joe Cornish, in a smashing debut. Keep an eye on John Boyega, 19, a fireball with serious acting skills. He plays Moses, the leader of a gang that mugs a nurse (Jodie Whittaker) and ends up the block's only chance against furry aliens with Day-Glo chompers and startling symbolic heft. OK, no more spoilers. This movie wants and needs to come at you like a beast in the dark. Allow it." -Peter Travers, Rolling Stone

item.description:
Midsummer Enchantment
Summer is almost over but it's not too late to enjoy summery makeup looks. Because it can get really hot (and sometimes humid depending on where you live) this tutorial is going to show you how to prevent smudging, smearing, creasing and all the ways the heat can mess up your makeup. Visit HauteLook.com here http://bit.ly/HauteLookJuly Remember, mineral makeup is water resistant, not waterproof. Using waterproof mascara will prevent your mascara from smudging from the humidity. Using eyeshadow primer will prevent creasing and keep your eye shadows lasting longer.
